<DocsLayout title="Checklists" section="Auxiliary Modules">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Checklists ensure your technicians perform all required tasks and maintain quality standards.
    They help track what needs to be done and guarantee work is completed according to your specifications.
  </p>
  <p>
    Field Promax's customizable checklists ensure technicians complete all tasks accurately
    the first time, eliminating rework and maintaining consistent standards.
  </p>

  <h2>How to Access</h2>
  <img src="/images/auxiliary-modules/auxillarymodules_checklist_01.webp" alt="Create Checklist" />
  <ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Manage Lists</strong> → <strong>Job Types and Checklist</strong></li>
    <li>Create a Job Type</li>
    <li>Define a checklist specifically for that Job Type</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Using Checklists</h2>

  <h3>Automatic Attachment</h3>
  <img src="/images/auxiliary-modules/auxillarymodules_checklist_03.webp" alt="Checklist in Work Order" />
  <p>
    When a work order is created with a selected Job Type, the corresponding checklist
    is automatically attached.
  </p>

  <h3>Work Order-Specific Tasks</h3>
  <p>
    From the work order, navigate to the <strong>Checklist</strong> tab at the bottom
    to add any additional tasks specific to that order.
  </p>

  <h3>Mobile App Completion</h3>
  <p>
    Technicians complete checklists using the mobile app:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Open the work order</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Other</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Select <strong>Checklist</strong> to complete items on-site</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>PDF Export</h3>
  <p>
    Generate a PDF version of the completed checklist to send directly to the customer.
  </p>

  <h2>Checklist Workflow</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Administrator creates Job Type with checklist</li>
    <li>Work order created with that Job Type</li>
    <li>Checklist automatically attached</li>
    <li>Technician completes checklist on mobile app</li>
    <li>PDF exported if needed for customer</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Technicians receive notifications for required checklist tasks</li>
    <li>Only <strong>Administrators</strong> can create and attach checklists</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Always complete the checklist</strong> for each job to maintain consistent quality.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Create checklists per Job Type</strong> to ensure relevant tasks are always included.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Export PDFs</strong> for customer documentation and proof of completed work.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
